   b. Research Restrictions: The Licensed Material may be used for research purposes only by individuals employed by public institutions such as universities, and for research primarily funded by public sources. Any research projects primarily funded by industry or commercial entities are expressly prohibited from using the Licensed Material. Academic researchers with partial industry funding or collaboration may use the Licensed Material, provided that the industry funding or involvement is not the primary source of support for the specific research project using the Licensed Material. Researchers employed by or fully funded by industry are not permitted to use the Licensed Material without separate express written permission from the Licensor.

   c. Open Access Requirement: Unless expressly waived in writing by the Licensor, any intellectual property resulting from the use of the Licensed Material, including but not limited to research findings, derived models, and modifications to the original code, must be made openly available under a non-commercial license compatible with these terms.

   d. Exceptions: The Licensor reserves the right to grant exceptions to any of the above restrictions on a case-by-case basis. Such exceptions must be obtained in writing from the Licensor and may be subject to additional terms.

4. Derived Works:
   Any works derived from or incorporating the Licensed Material must be released under this same license or a compatible non-commercial, open license that includes all restrictions specified herein.

5. Attribution:
